### Test WhatsApp Message Sending

### 1. Send a test template message to Tebogo (Quick Test)
POST http://localhost:8082/api/whatsapp/send-test
Content-Type: application/json

###

### 2. Send a custom text message
POST http://localhost:8082/api/whatsapp/send-text
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "to": "27662035457",
  "message": "Hello from Infobip! This is a test message from your Spring Boot application."
}

###

### 3. Send a custom template message
POST http://localhost:8082/api/whatsapp/send-template
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "to": "27662035457",
  "templateName": "test_whatsapp_template_en",
  "language": "en",
  "placeholders": ["Tebogo"]
}

###

### 4. Check Swagger UI
# Open in browser: http://localhost:8082/swagger-ui/index.html

###

### 5. Check H2 Console
# Open in browser: http://localhost:8082/h2-console
# JDBC URL: jdbc:h2:mem:testdb
# Username: sa
# Password: password
